Nov 25 2009 	Fantastic Boutique Hotel in the Heart of Union Square	I was in San Francisco for two weeks on business in November 2009. After the first week, I decided to move from the Good Hotel (about 10 min from Union Square) to Hotel Union Square.I stayed in an &quot;executive&quot; suite on the 6th floor (room 604) facing the street. The front desk mentioned the &quot;noise&quot; being moderate, but aside from the trolley bells, only the lightest of sleepers would be disturbed by the sounds below.The room itself was pretty great. Wide and spacious, the bed was incredibly comfortable, and the bathroom was immaculate. The showerhead in particular was impressive. This is easily one of those rooms you could spend all day in comfortably.Like most boutique hotels, I found the staff to be incredibly friendly and attentive. They stored my bags before check-in while my room was being cleaned, and brought them up barely 2 min after I walked into the room. All of my requests were answered immediately.Since you're in the middle of Union Square, there's a ton of food and shopping around. Not a lot open 24 hours, but Lori's Diner is right across the street if you really need pancakes at 2am.The nearby Starbucks - up about a half block - opens at 4am (a nice perk) and just down the street from there are a line of taxis you can use to get to wherever you're going, assuming it's too far to walk.Overall, staying here was an absolute pleasure, and thanks to Orbitz I managed to stay in an amazing suite for about $160 / night.Highly recommended for both first-time and returning travelers.	
Nov 14 2009 	Perfect location Comfy bed - right in the heart of San Francisco	We were worried after reading other reviews, but were pleasantly surprised! The rooms are small, definitely not a chain hotel, but that is not what we were looking for. Our room was facing Powell - we woke to the trolley bell in the morning and fell asleep to the sounds of the city every night - NOT unpleasant or disturbing. Great location - easy access to the BART, trolleys, cable cars, busses - all within a block or two at most. Car rental was two blocks away - easy trip to Sonoma and coastal Route 1. Tom (concierge) and Tony (front desk) welcomed us and made us feel at home - always pleasant, always helpful - We loved it here and will definitely stay again...................	
