Oct 3 2009 	Great location 	This hotel is difficult to rate overall as it's a bit of a mixed bag, so please bear with me and consider my comments.Good points: 1) Great location - right in the thick of things in the city. Great restaurants and bars nearby and near the shops. 2) Great decor - this hotel is fitted-out very nicely. It's contemporary, yet sympathetic to its age. 3) The front desk service is very good - the guys are keen to help and to make you feel at home.Bad points: 1) The rooms get SO hot it's unbelievable. I'd just come from Vegas and the rooms felt hotter than it was outside there! There's no air-conditioning and the hotel seems to conduct heat like crazy! 2) It's very noisy. Now this would be less of a problem if there was air conditioning as you could shut the windows. Nevertheless, there is a lot of road noise and then there are deliveries throughout the night - the result is the worst night sleep I have EVER had. 3) The rooms are WAY smaller than they appear on the internet! There wasn't even enough room for me to lay my suitcase on the stand! Overall very cramped - this may not be a huge problem if the website was more clear about this and you could get a good night's sleep. 4) Toiletries not replaced. Although the room was well cleaned and linen changed each day, there was no replacement of shower gel, shampoo or soap each day - I don't think that's good enough.Overall I don't think I'd recommend this hotel to anyone as there are better competitors at the same or lower price. If they sorted the air conditioning, I may change my mind.	
