Jun 24 2009 	The Total San Francisco Experience	We stayed for six nights at the Hotel Union Square while touring the City and attending to some art business. It's located in THE heart of San Francisco, meaning that it offered us nothing less than TOTAL immersion in the life of the City. We read the reviews about the cable car noise and were undaunted. I mean, come on. What is the most recognizable symbol of San Francisco other than the Cable Car? If it's running past on the street down below your window where else would you be? San Francisco is a world-class city and it's people offered us nothing less than a walk across the entire planet in terms of the languages they spoke, the food they offered in restaurants, and the charm of mashing literally dozens of cultures together into a relatively small place. We were able to walk everywhere or we could jump on any one of the six forms of public transportation within a block and a half of the Hotel. The immediate area offered unbelievable shopping and we took Cable Cars and Antique Street Cars to the Embarcadero and Fisherman's Wharf. The staff at Hotel Union Square presented themselves with complete professionalism the entire time we stayed. Tom greeted us each early morning with smiles and a ready suggestion based on our questions. The desk staff assisted us with boarding passes on our way out of town. We didn't rent a car because we wanted to have the entire urban experience, but the hotel has a large parking lot on the rear of the property where a friend visiting from Santa Cruz parked her car for a very reasonable rate. We're going back to San Francisco as soon as we can and we're going to book Hotel Union Square without a doubt.	
