Jan 6 2009	Excellent location a few housekeeping hiccups	Hotel Union Square is a nice boutique property one block off Powell &amp; Market - no need to even THINK about a car, you're steps away from MUNI, BART, and the world-famous Cable Cars.I stayed 12/27-12/30 for a vacation in room 427.A lot of people note room size. It's SF. If you book a cheap hotel rate, you're going to have a small room. If you want a big room, you'll need to pay for it.THE PROS:**Location, location, location! SF is a very walkable city, and many attractions and activities are steps from the Hotel Union Square**Ambience! Some reviewers didn't like it, but I thought it was quite fun to open my window and hear a cable car rumbling / dinging by.**Killer internet prepaid rate. Very reasonable rate for that neighborhood.THE CONS:**Couple of hiccups with housekeeping - my room had not been properly serviced on check in, there were no fresh toiletries in the bath, and the prior guest's half-consumed bottle of water was on the desk**Front Desk hiccups. Room was not available at 3pm (that's OK, check-in is 4) ... and when I advised desk staff about my lack of toiletries and cleaning, the clerk suggested I might have left the &quot;do not disturb&quot; sign out the evening prior - which would have been plausible except that I'd noted I'd checked in the evening prior.**I stayed in the &quot;Annex&quot; portion - which did not have the same feel and decor as the &quot;Main&quot; area of the hotel. My next stay, I'll make sure to ask for a non-Annex room.**No view whatsoever. None. A fire escape and a wall. Oh well - it was a cheap rate!All in all, it was exactly what I'd paid for. A nice place to sleep with a great location. The issues with housekeeping, desk staff, and a generally uninspired room kept me from rating a bit higher.	
