rs. And there sat my bag. When I mentioned it to the clerk, she was very rude and said, &quot;We keep our eye on your bag at all times.&quot; Which was amazing, since I had stood at the counter for 10 minutes without anyone looking up or acknowledging me while they took phone calls and talked about restaurants with two other guests. When I arrived home, I complained to their management. Who offered NO DISCOUNT for my troubled stay, but did offer one free night if I ever came back. (Because they know no way would I ever take them up on it.) Dirty hotel. Ugly staff to match. What the heck are these other reviewers thinking? PS - I travel alot. Read my other reviews. You will know this hotel has to be pretty awful to get such a negative review.	
May 4 2007 	Great Location..Ask for courtyard facing room.	We booked this hotel for the weekend and got a great rate from Travelzoo ($89 a night). Checkin staff were friendly and efficient.The PROS: The best thing about the hotel is its location. If you enjoy shopping, this hotel is probably in the best possible spot. It is also a block away from the BART station so getting to and from the airport is a breeze. The hotel is also close to bus/tram stops that take you to all the major tourist attractions and restaurants. The hotel is in the central tourist shopping area so it is safe to walk around in even at night. The bed was pretty comfortable and the room was small but clean. For $89 a night we were happy with the room. Its definitely not the Four Seasons but for the price we thought that it was definitely worth what we paid for. We also like the free wireless internet and free coffee in the morning.The CONS: Make sure you ask for a Courtyard facing room. We were given a room facing the street and the garbage truck come in at around 2am and somehow the banging did not stop till 5am. Then the sounds of traffic and the tram starts. We brought ear plugs cause we knew this might happen. But I can see some people get extremely irritated if they do not come prepared. The next night we transferred to a courtyard facing room and it was very quiet. The hotel is in a fairly old converted apartment building so there is only one elevator and the layout of the rooms is a bit weird at times.Nice extras-There is a Walgreen across the street so you can easily buy snacks, drinks, etc. if you need it. The room we got had a bag full of travel essential samples and it did come in handy. There is an Enterprise Car Rental place 1 block away at Hotel Nikko and we were able to rent a car there and drive to Sonoma for an overnight trip.	
Apr 24 2007	Great Value Overall Would stay there again	This hotel is a great bargain for the location. It has great access to public transportation (the cable car runs right out front) and the bus line and underground are only a two block walk away. Yes, it can be noisy, but I think that's par for the course with an older building. Ask for an interior room and the noise is greatly cut down. Don't worry about missing out on a view, as all you would really see is the street even if you were in an outside room, the sacrifice is well worth it. The staff was overall very helpful and friendly. Tom (contrary to some other reports) was wonderful and offered great advice.The room was very clean, the beds comfy and the little toiletries and sample packs were nice. There were also a couple of complimentary bottles of water. There isn't any air conditioning, but the room was very comfortable with the windows open.The hotel has free wireless access all over the hotel, a laptop with internet access in the lobby that is free, morning coffee and a free wine happy hour from 5-6. While you are in San Francisco, be sure to check out Beach Blanket Babylon in North Beach. This was a great show, well worth the price and the wait (you need to get there well in advance to get a good seat). Also, the Ferry to Sausalito provides a great view of the entire skyline and Sausalito is a nice place to window shop. If you are in on a Saturday, stroll down to the Farmers Market, the assortment of fresh vegetables, fruits, breads, cheeses, flowers, etc is wonderful.	
