Mar 13 2007 	Can't wait to come back	I needed a mid-winter escape, and didn't want to be stuck in the usual generic hotel room. From the minute I got to the Hotel Union Square, I knew that I'd made a great choice. I loved the original art in the halls and in my room. Although my room was small, for one person it was fine, and warmed up quickly when I turned up the heat. It looked more like a bedroom than a hotel room, with funky, homey furnishings. Sometimes the old steam pipes were noisy, but it didn't bother me. The staff was friendly and professional, and Tom, the concierge, was the absolute best. All I had to do was ask about walking tours of the city,and before I knew it he'd assembled a fat stack of schedules and routes for me. He also knew the best places to get whatever kind of food I was in the mood for. The wine receptions in the evening were a nice touch, as was the coffee in the morning. The hotel's location at the end of the Powell Street line makes this a great base for touring and shopping, since it's close to the visitor center, the cable cars, the bus lines, and BART.	
